  1040→## 4. Validation Strategy
  1041→
  1042→### 4.1 Validation Chain Details
  1043→
  1044→| Field | Endpoint | Rules | Sanitization |
  1045→|-------|----------|-------|--------------|
  1046→| `title` | POST, PUT | Required (POST), 1-200 chars | trim(), escape() |
  1047→| `description` | POST, PUT | Optional, max 2000 chars, nullable | trim(), escape() |
  1048→| `status` | POST, PUT, GET | Optional, enum validation | none |
  1049→| `id` | GET, PUT, DELETE | UUID v4 format | trim() |
  1050→| `limit` | GET | Optional, 1-100, default 20 | toInt() |
  1051→| `offset` | GET | Optional, >= 0, default 0 | toInt() |
  1052→| `sortBy` | GET | Optional, createdAt or updatedAt | none |
  1053→| `order` | GET | Optional, asc or desc | none |
  1054→
  1055→### 4.2 Custom Validators
  1056→
  1057→**UUID Validator**:
  1058→```typescript
  1059→const UUID_REGEX = /^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-4[0-9a-f]{3}-[89ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$/i;
  1060→
  1061→.custom((value) => {
  1062→  if (!UUID_REGEX.test(value)) {
  1063→    throw new Error('Invalid task ID format');
  1064→  }
  1065→  return true;
  1066→})
  1067→```
  1068→
  1069→**Nullable String Validator** (for description update):
  1070→```typescript
  1071→.custom((value) => {
  1072→  if (value === null) return true;
  1073→  if (typeof value !== 'string') {
  1074→    throw new Error('Description must be a string or null');
  1075→  }
  1076→  return true;
  1077→})
  1078→```
  1079→
  1080→### 4.3 Error Message Mapping
  1081→
  1082→| Scenario | Error Message |
  1083→|----------|---------------|
  1084→| Missing title | "Title is required" |
  1085→| Empty title (whitespace only) | "Title must be at least 1 character" |
  1086→| Title too long | "Title must be at most 200 characters" |
  1087→| Description too long | "Description must be at most 2000 characters" |
  1088→| Invalid status | "Status must be one of: pending, in_progress, completed" |
  1089→| Invalid UUID | "Invalid task ID format" |
  1090→| Invalid limit | "Limit must be between 1 and 100" |
  1091→| Invalid offset | "Offset must be a non-negative integer" |
